\section{Experimental Proposals}
\begin{itemize}
    \item **Precision magnetometers / SQUID arrays**: search for periodic oscillating magnetic fields ($B_{\rm obs} \sim 10^{-24}$ T) over extended periods.
    \item **High-energy collider experiments**: transient monopole excitations in lattice perturbations, energy scale $\sim 70$ GeV.
    \item **Astrophysical observations**: cumulative effect of ultra-rare monopoles in neutron stars or magnetars could produce detectable anomalies.
\end{itemize}

\section{Conclusion}
Hamiltonian Crystal monopoles are low-energy topological excitations, naturally arising from the lattice of vacuum Fock-space modes. The model provides **falsifiable predictions**, including rare but measurable magnetic signals and transient high-energy monopoles. This opens a novel experimental avenue for testing both dark-sector physics and topological excitations in a controlled framework.

